# Section 15 — Future Roadmap & Evolution

---

# 15.1 Introduction

The current implementation of the Study Abroad Finder successfully demonstrates a modular AI application built using Google ADK and the Model Context Protocol (MCP).

The system supports:

- Google Gemini 2.5 Flash
- Multiple MCP Servers
- Local and Remote Tool Integration
- Docker Deployment
- Cloud Hosting
- AI-assisted University Recommendations

While the application is fully functional, it also serves as a strong architectural foundation for significantly more advanced AI systems.

This chapter outlines the logical evolution of the project from a Proof of Concept into an enterprise-grade AI platform.

---

# 15.2 Current Architecture

The current system architecture is shown below.

```
                    User

                     │

                     ▼

                  Browser

                     │

                     ▼

                   Flask

                     │

                     ▼

                Google ADK

                     │

                     ▼

              Gemini 2.5 Flash

                     │

      ┌──────────────┼──────────────┐

      ▼              ▼              ▼

 Tavily MCP    Google Maps MCP   Scholarship MCP

                     │

                     ▼

              Filesystem MCP
```

This architecture is modular and extensible.

However, several enhancements can significantly improve scalability and enterprise readiness.

